Volume 38 of the series Operations Research/Computer Science Interfaces Series pp 1-18 Planned Route Optimization For Real-Time Vehicle Routing Soumia Ichoua1 Affiliated with Département d’opérations et systèmes de décisions and Centre de recherche sur lestechnologies de l’organisation réseau, Pavillon Palasis-Prince, Université Laval , Michel Gendreau Affiliated with Département d’informatique et de recherche opérationnelle and Centre de recherche sur les transports, Université de Montréal , Jean-Yves Potvin Affiliated with Département d’informatique et de recherche opérationnelle and Centre de recherche sur les transports, Université de Montréal This paper reviews and classifies the work done in the field of dynamic vehicle routing. We focus, in particular, on problems where the uncertainty comes from the occurrence of new requests. Problem-solving approaches are investigated in contexts where consolidation of multiple requests onto the same vehicle is allowed and addressed through the design of planned routes. Starting with pure myopic approaches, we then review in later sections the issues of diversion and anticipation of future requests Keywords real-time vehicle routing planned routes diversion anticipation